dct_description_sm: Likely part of the Geologische Karte von Preussen und den Thüringischen Staaten, published by Prussian government. Does not include newer numbering (i.e. Waake sheet 4426)
Relief shown by contours and spot heights
Any information in margins cut off in mounting
2 bar scales in meters/"Schritt" and "geographische Meile"
Shows topography, forests, towns (with buildings and roads), various types of routes or paths, waterways (colored in blue)
Title and scale information glued on panel: "Waake. Maaſsstab 1/25000 der natürlichen Länge"
Edges of map indicate adjacent sheets, with horizontal sheets "2520 (Göttingen)" and "2522 (Duderstadt)" and vertical sheets "2448 (Lindau)" and "2554 (Gelliehausen)"
